        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer369681012" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12674065431990400121">Thanks to goodreads and Mr. Angelo for this First Reads giveaway!<br/>I like the story line. It&apos;s fun and exciting. I also like the main character, Crystalon. From the very beginning the book is well-paced.<br/>However, the book is full of those grammatical errors (punctuation, awkward tense changes) that seem to plague independently published works. I&apos;m not trying to dismiss all indies, but an editor is important, even if s/he isn&apos;t a professional. I guess in the end I&apos;d like to give it 2.5 stars because</span>
  <span id="freeText12674065431990400121" style="display:none">Thanks to goodreads and Mr. Angelo for this First Reads giveaway!<br />I like the story line. It's fun and exciting. I also like the main character, Crystalon. From the very beginning the book is well-paced.<br />However, the book is full of those grammatical errors (punctuation, awkward tense changes) that seem to plague independently published works. I'm not trying to dismiss all indies, but an editor is important, even if s/he isn't a professional. I guess in the end I'd like to give it 2.5 stars because it's just not as well edited as my 3 star books.</span>
