  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/720325608" />
    <a title="Kris Richards" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/20031678-kris-richards"><img alt="Kris Richards" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1367662643p2/20031678.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/720325608?book_show_action=true">Sep 15, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kris Richards" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kris Richards" href="/user/show/20031678-kris-richards">Kris Richards</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780615763033" href="/book/show/17335397-redemption-of-the-sorcerer">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer720325608" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9894278136625842259">Pointed in the direction of this book by my wife (who knows I enjoy Harry Potter, David Haydn, and the old ‘Flashman’ books) and I’m glad that she did. This is a very easy read that the reader is able to pick up and put down really easily. I found myself reading this on the train to work, at the office (when quiet!) and then again walking home from the train station. With characters that are relatable and real, I was able to connect to the story and the urgency of their actions. This is a book t</span>
  <span id="freeText9894278136625842259" style="display:none">Pointed in the direction of this book by my wife (who knows I enjoy Harry Potter, David Haydn, and the old ‘Flashman’ books) and I’m glad that she did. This is a very easy read that the reader is able to pick up and put down really easily. I found myself reading this on the train to work, at the office (when quiet!) and then again walking home from the train station. With characters that are relatable and real, I was able to connect to the story and the urgency of their actions. This is a book that straddles fantasy and adventure and I think it would be appeal to the teenage readership – especially teenage boys – and if the author continues to put out books like this, I think he’ll do very well. </span>
  <a data-text-id="9894278136625842259" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


